Tercero

Acerca del empleo
🚀 We’re looking for an IT Asset Management Analyst to join our team! 🚀


Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree or minimum of five years of relevant work experience.
Proven experience in Asset Management.
Strong communication skills to coordinate with team members, vendors, and management.
Proficiency using the Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, etc).
Excellent organization, project management, and time management skills.
Experience in working with Telecom technology is a plus.
Experience managing large-scale Real Estate technology programs supporting the overall workspace experience.
Demonstrated ability to lead complex programs requiring high-level stakeholder engagement across multiple organizations.
Collaborative leadership with the ability to manage multiple priorities and resolve issues innovatively.
Strong platform experience with leading collaboration technologies (certifications are a plus).
Experience with wireless deployments and SD-WAN is a plus.
Responsibilities:

Lead and manage IT Asset Management initiatives across the organization.
Coordinate with internal teams, vendors, and management to ensure seamless execution of asset strategies.
Oversee technology programs aligned with workspace and real estate initiatives.
Ensure compliance with internal policies and industry best practices.
Track and report on project milestones, risks, and progress.
Support technology deployments including wireless and SDWAN where applicable.
Provide effective communication and documentation throughout the project lifecycle.


Required Languages:

English Upper intermediate (51–79%)


Job Location(s):

Hybrid, Bogotá – Colombia


